Summary: Provides methods for accessing and modifying FABRIK joint properties within a SkeletonModification2D node.

Method: get_fabrik_joint_bone2d_node(joint_idx: int) → NodePath
Returns the Bone2D node associated with the specified FABRIK joint index.

Method: get_fabrik_joint_bone_index(joint_idx: int) → int
Returns the bone index associated with the specified FABRIK joint index.

Method: get_fabrik_joint_magnet_position(joint_idx: int) → Vector2
Returns the magnet position of the specified FABRIK joint index.

Method: get_fabrik_joint_use_target_rotation(joint_idx: int) → bool
Returns whether the target rotation is used for the specified FABRIK joint index.

Method: set_fabrik_joint_bone2d_node(joint_idx: int, bone2d_nodepath: NodePath)
Sets the Bone2D node for the specified FABRIK joint index.

Method: set_fabrik_joint_bone_index(joint_idx: int, bone_idx: int)
Sets the bone index for the specified FABRIK joint index.

Method: set_fabrik_joint_magnet_position(joint_idx: int, magnet_position: Vector2)
Sets the magnet position for the specified FABRIK joint index.

Method: set_fabrik_joint_use_target_rotation(joint_idx: int, use_target_rotation: bool)
Sets whether the target rotation is used for the specified FABRIK joint index.
